Blocks.childText: CHURCH MEETINGS. 5 AUTUMN. 8s & 7s. D. SPANISH. 1. Glo-rious things of thee are spok en, Zi - on, ci - ty of our God! FINE. He whose word can-not be brok - en, Formed thee for his own a - bode. D. S With Sal - va tion's walls sur-round-ed, Thou may'st smile at all thy foes. D. S. On the rock of A - ges found-ed, What can shake thy sure re pose? c/'s 8s & 7s. D. 1sa. 33. 20. 21. NEWTON. 162. Zion is defended and supplied. 4 Blest inhabitants of Zion, 2 See the streams of living waters Wash'd in the Redeemer's blood Springing from eternal love, Jesus, whom their souls rely on, Well supply thy sons and daughters, Makes them kings and priests to God; And all fear of want remove: 'Tis his love his people raises Who can faint while such a river Over self to reign as kings, Ever flows their thirst t'assuage? And as priests, his solemn praises Grace, which like the Lord, the giver, Each for a thank-off'ring brings. Never fails from age to age. 3 Round each habitation hov'ring, 5 Saviour, if of Zion's city See the cloud and fire appear! I, through grace, a member am; For a glory and a cov'ring, Let the world deride or pity, Showing that the Lord is near; I will glory in thy name: Thus deriving from their banner Fading is the wordling's pleasure, Light by night and shade by day; All his boasted pomp and show; Safe they feed upon the Manna Solid joys and lasting treasure, Which he gives them when they pray. None but Zion's children know.
